WEBVTT

00:00.300 --> 00:03.934
Quorum — the Nonprofit Board OS.

00:04.234 --> 00:17.252
Stage three moves the foundation into the real world: a bank account, sensible spending
rules, and insurance. Open the checklist, and scroll to Banking, Signatories and
Insurance.

00:17.552 --> 00:29.994
First: open the corporate bank account. The bank will ask for three things — the stamped
Articles, the E I N letter, and a signed Board Resolution naming who's allowed to sign.

00:30.294 --> 00:42.400
That resolution is already waiting in your Documents library — the Board Resolution and
Written Consent. Fill in the bank details, have the directors sign it, and bring it
along.

00:42.700 --> 00:56.198
Second: set the two-signature rule — the dollar amount above which two people must
approve a payment. Many small nonprofits pick around twenty-five hundred dollars. Record
it in the minutes.

00:56.498 --> 01:07.644
Third: insurance. Get quotes for directors-and-officers coverage, and general liability.
It protects the very people who volunteered to serve.

01:07.944 --> 01:18.178
Three steps — honestly, one good errand day. Next: stage four. Tax exemption, and
charitable registration.
